<h1>Invoices</h1>
<p>Here you have centralised, permanent access to your IATA electronic invoices as well as access
to your historical information (starting from May 2006).</p>
<p>Please note that invoices are issued centrally in Montreal and therefore do not include VAT
charges. You will thus need to self-assess the VAT on the purchase, using so-called "reverse charge
mechanism".</p>
<p>Each of the electronic invoices issued by IATA is electronically signed in compliance with the
national provision in the law of EU Directive 2001/115/EC. If you want to verify the electronic
signature, you need to download 
<a
href="http://localhost:80/PortalDocroot/certificates/cis/eu/ANCERTCNC.crt"
 target="_blank">
<u>
<font color="#0000ff">Certificate 1</font>
</u>
</a> and 
<a
href="http://localhost:80/PortalDocroot/certificates/cis/eu/ANCERTNOT.crt"
 target="_blank">
<u>
<font color="#0000ff">Certificate 2</font>
</u>
</a> . Instructions on how to verify can also be 
<a target="_blank"
href="http://localhost:80/PortalDocroot/cms/sites/default/static/document/en/application/cis/general/SSP/installation.pdf">
<u>
<font color="#0000ff">downloaded here</font>
</u>
</a>.</p>
